  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Carnival sponsor management allows you to link sponsors to specific carnival events, set sponsorship levels, manage sponsor benefits, and control how sponsors are displayed for your event.</p>

  <h3>Carnival vs Club Sponsors</h3>

  <h4>Carnival Sponsors</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Event-Specific</strong> — Sponsors linked to a particular carnival event</li>
    <li><strong>Sponsorship Levels</strong> — Platinum, Gold, Silver, Bronze, Supporting tiers</li>
    <li><strong>Financial Tracking</strong> — Sponsorship values and package details</li>
    <li><strong>Display Control</strong> — Control logo size, display order, and visibility</li>
    <li><strong>Program Inclusion</strong> — Option to include in carnival program and website</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Club Sponsors</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Club-Level</strong> — Sponsors associated with your club generally</li>
    <li><strong>Public Visibility</strong> — Can be displayed on club profile pages</li>
    <li><strong>Logo Management</strong> — Basic logo and contact information</li>
    <li><strong>Website Links</strong> — Direct links to sponsor websites</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Accessing Carnival Sponsor Management</h3>

  <h4>From Carnival Management</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Open Your Carnival</strong> — Navigate to your carnival event page</li>
    <li><strong>Access Management</strong> — Click "Manage Carnival" or similar management option</li>
    <li><strong>Find Sponsors Section</strong> — Look for "Sponsors" in the management menu</li>
    <li><strong>View Current Sponsors</strong> — See all sponsors currently linked to your carnival</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Direct Access</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>URL Navigation</strong> — Go directly to `/carnivals/[carnival-id]/sponsors`</li>
    <li><strong>Dashboard Shortcut</strong> — Access through your carnival dashboard</li>
    <li><strong>Quick Actions</strong> — Use management shortcuts from carnival listings</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Managing Carnival Sponsors</h3>

  <h4>Viewing Current Sponsors</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sponsor List</strong> — See all sponsors linked to your carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Sponsorship Levels</strong> — View sponsorship tiers (Platinum, Gold, Silver, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Logo Display</strong> — Preview how sponsor logos appear</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Information</strong> — Access sponsor contact details</li>
    <li><strong>Display Order</strong> — See the order sponsors appear in listings</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Adding Sponsors to Carnivals</h4>

  <h5>From Existing Sponsors</h5>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Access Add Sponsor</strong> — Click "Add Sponsor" from the carnival sponsors page</li>
    <li><strong>Select Sponsor</strong> — Choose from your club's existing sponsors or browse all sponsors</li>
    <li><strong>Set Sponsorship Level</strong> — Choose Platinum, Gold, Silver, Bronze, or Supporting</li>
    <li><strong>Configure Details</strong> — Set sponsorship value, display options, and benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Save Relationship</strong> — Create the carnival-sponsor relationship</li>
  </ol>

  <h5>Sponsorship Level Details</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Platinum</strong> — Highest tier with premium benefits and prominent display</li>
    <li><strong>Gold</strong> — High-tier sponsorship with enhanced visibility</li>
    <li><strong>Silver</strong> — Mid-tier sponsorship with standard benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Bronze</strong> — Entry-level sponsorship with basic recognition</li>
    <li><strong>Supporting</strong> — Recognition sponsorship with minimal financial commitment</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Configuring Sponsor Benefits</h4>

  <h5>Financial Tracking</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sponsorship Value</strong> — Record the monetary value of the sponsorship</li>
    <li><strong>Package Details</strong> — Document what the sponsor receives for their investment</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Tracking</strong> — Note payment status and terms</li>
    <li><strong>Contract Details</strong> — Record agreement terms and conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Display and Visibility</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Logo Display Size</strong> — Choose Small, Medium, or Large logo display</li>
    <li><strong>Display Order</strong> — Set the order sponsors appear in listings</li>
    <li><strong>Program Inclusion</strong> — Choose whether to include in carnival program</li>
    <li><strong>Website Display</strong> — Control visibility on carnival website</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Sponsor Display Management</h3>

  <h4>Logo Display Options</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Small</strong> — Compact logo display for listings and secondary mentions</li>
    <li><strong>Medium</strong> — Standard logo size for general sponsor displays</li>
    <li><strong>Large</strong> — Prominent logo display for major sponsors</li>
    <li><strong>Custom Sizing</strong> — Some systems allow custom logo dimensions</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Display Order Management</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Priority Ordering</strong> — Higher sponsorship levels typically appear first</li>
    <li><strong>Custom Ordering</strong> — Manually adjust display order as needed</li>
    <li><strong>Alphabetical Fallback</strong> — Sponsors without specific ordering use alphabetical sorting</li>
    <li><strong>Dynamic Updates</strong> — Change order without affecting sponsorship relationships</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Visibility Controls</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Program Inclusion</strong> — Control whether sponsors appear in printed programs</li>
    <li><strong>Website Display</strong> — Manage online visibility and prominence</li>
    <li><strong>Public vs Private</strong> — Some sponsorships may be private arrangements</li>
    <li><strong>Temporal Control</strong> — Show sponsors only during active sponsorship periods</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Removing Sponsors from Carnivals</h3>

  <h4>Safe Removal Process</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Access Sponsor</strong> — Find the sponsor you want to remove</li>
    <li><strong>Review Relationship</strong> — Check sponsorship details and any dependencies</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Removal</strong> — Use the remove button (usually requires confirmation)</li>
    <li><strong>Update Records</strong> — Note the removal in your records if necessary</li>
    <li><strong>Notify Sponsor</strong> — Inform the sponsor of the relationship termination</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Removal Considerations</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contract Obligations</strong> — Ensure removal doesn't violate sponsorship agreements</li>
    <li><strong>Display Updates</strong> — Remove sponsor from programs, websites, and materials</li>
    <li><strong>Refund Arrangements</strong> — Handle any refund or adjustment arrangements</li>
    <li><strong>Future Opportunities</strong> — Keep communication open for future sponsorships</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Sponsor Communication Management</h3>

  <h4>Maintaining Sponsor Relationships</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Regular Updates</strong> — Keep sponsors informed about carnival progress</li>
    <li><strong>Benefit Fulfillment</strong> — Ensure sponsors receive promised benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Recognition</strong> — Provide appropriate recognition and acknowledgment</li>
    <li><strong>Feedback Collection</strong> — Gather sponsor feedback on carnival organization</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Sponsor Benefits Tracking</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Logo Display</strong> — Ensure logos appear as promised</li>
    <li><strong>Mention Opportunities</strong> — Provide verbal and written acknowledgments</li>
    <li><strong>Program Inclusion</strong> — Include sponsors in carnival programs and materials</li>
    <li><strong>Networking Opportunities</strong> — Facilitate connections with teams and attendees</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Advanced Sponsor Management</h3>

  <h4>Multi-Carnival Sponsors</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Relationship Management</strong> — Handle sponsors who support multiple carnivals</li>
    <li><strong>Benefit Coordination</strong> — Coordinate benefits across different events</li>
    <li><strong>Communication Efficiency</strong> — Streamline communications for recurring sponsors</li>
    <li><strong>Long-term Planning</strong> — Develop ongoing sponsorship relationships</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Sponsorship Analytics</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Value Tracking</strong> — Monitor sponsorship revenue and value</li>
    <li><strong>ROI Assessment</strong> — Evaluate return on investment for sponsors</li>
    <li><strong>Engagement Metrics</strong> — Track sponsor interaction and satisfaction</li>
    <li><strong>Renewal Planning</strong> — Identify opportunities for sponsorship renewal</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Best Practices for Carnival Sponsors</h3>

  <h4>Sponsorship Acquisition</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Clear Value Proposition</strong> — Clearly communicate sponsor benefits and visibility</li>
    <li><strong>Tiered Options</strong> — Offer different sponsorship levels to suit various budgets</li>
    <li><strong>Early Engagement</strong> — Approach potential sponsors well in advance</li>
    <li><strong>Professional Proposals</strong> — Provide detailed sponsorship packages and terms</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Relationship Management</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Regular Communication</strong> — Maintain ongoing dialogue with sponsors</li>
    <li><strong>Benefit Delivery</strong> — Consistently deliver promised sponsorship benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Recognition</strong> — Provide appropriate acknowledgment and thanks</li>
    <li><strong>Feedback Loop</strong> — Seek and act on sponsor feedback</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Operational Excellence</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accurate Records</strong> — Maintain detailed records of all sponsorship arrangements</li>
    <li><strong>Timeline Management</strong> — Meet all sponsorship-related deadlines</li>
    <li><strong>Quality Control</strong> — Ensure high-quality execution of sponsor benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Contingency Planning</strong> — Have backup plans for sponsorship-related issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Troubleshooting Sponsor Issues</h3>

  <h4>Common Issues</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Logo Display Problems</strong> — Ensure logos are properly formatted and accessible</li>
    <li><strong>Missing Benefits</strong> — Track and fulfill all promised sponsorship benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Communication Gaps</strong> — Maintain regular contact with all sponsors</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Issues</strong> — Handle sponsorship fees and payment arrangements</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Resolution Strategies</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Clear Documentation</strong> — Keep detailed records of all agreements and communications</li>
    <li><strong>Proactive Communication</strong> — Address potential issues before they become problems</li>
    <li><strong>Flexible Solutions</strong> — Be willing to adjust arrangements when reasonable</li>
    <li><strong>Professional Handling</strong> — Maintain professionalism in all sponsor interactions</li>
  </ul>

